# Phase 2.4 — Server-arbitrated collision resolution.
#
# Two players ram each other. Currently their clients independently simulate
# the impact → outcomes diverge. Worst case one player phases through the other.
# We make the server arbiter.
#
# Target files:
#   NEW: code/components/citizen-server-impl/src/state/CollisionArbiter.cpp
#   PATCH: code/components/extra-natives-five/src/CollisionTracking.cpp
#
# === Flow ===
#
# Both clients detect their own collision against an entity owned by another
# client. Both send to server: COLLISION_DETECTED {
#     ourVehicleId, theirVehicleId,
#     ourPreImpactState (pos, vel, ang_vel),
#     timestampClient
# }
#
# Server arbitrates:
# 1. Match the two reports (within 200 ms window).
# 2. Pick the more-recent of the two pre-impact states (less stale).
# 3. Run a single rigid-body collision math step on server.
# 4. Broadcast authoritative post-collision state to both clients (and observers).
# 5. Both clients soft-reconcile (Phase 1.3 hooks in here).
#
# === Math: simple Newtonian elastic-inelastic collision ===
#
# v1' = ((m1 - e*m2) * v1 + (1+e) * m2 * v2) / (m1 + m2)
# v2' = ((m2 - e*m1) * v2 + (1+e) * m1 * v1) / (m1 + m2)
#
# Where e = coefficient of restitution (e.g. 0.4 for car-to-car).
# Angular component derived from collision point relative to each car's center.
#
# === Damage ===
#
# Total kinetic energy lost = 0.5 * (m1 + m2) * (v_rel)² * (1 - e²)
# Distributed proportionally to each car's mass and incoming velocity.
#
# === Failure modes ===
#
# 1. Only one report arrives (other client crashed mid-collision): treat the
#    single-sided report as canonical.
# 2. Reports arrive > 200 ms apart: treat as two separate events (each car had
#    a follow-up collision with the other).
# 3. Disagreement on participant (A says hit B, B says hit C): trust raycast
#    on server using rewound positions.
#
# === Convars ===
#
#   sv_arbitratedCollisions       on|off   default ON (post-stabilization)
#   sv_collisionElasticity        0.0-1.0  default 0.4 (cars)
#   sv_collisionDamageMultiplier  0.5-2.0  default 1.0
#
# === Cost ===
#
# CPU: trivial (one math step per arbitrated collision; collisions are rare on a tick scale).
# Memory: 1 KB per active arbitration window (auto-released after broadcast).
